<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 05 at 4:44PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FREEZING DRIZZLE POSSIBLE ACROSS NORTHERN MASSACHUSETTS
AND CONNECTICUT TONIGHT INTO EARLY SUNDAY...
Widely scattered showers will move into the area overnight
tonight as a warm front lifts into southern New England. Temperatures
are expected to remain at or below freezing overnight along and north
of the Mass Pike and in the interior valley locations across northern
MA and CT. This may lead to patchy freezing drizzle and/or localized
freezing fog. Given the antecedent cold road surface temperatures,
patches of black ice may develop, particularly across bridges and
overpasses. Motorists are urged to drive with extra caution overnight
into the pre-dawn hours. Temperatures should rise above freezing by
sunrise, alleviating any of these issues.</description>
